de.opendiabetes.vault.nsapi

Class DataCursor

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.opendiabetes.vault.nsapi.DataCursor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<JsonElement>

    public class DataCursor
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<JsonElement>
    A buffer for Nightscout data. Lazily loads objects from the server as needed. The internal buffer is refreshed if it runs out of objects until the server does not return any more data.

                  java.lang.String dateField,
                  java.time.temporal.TemporalAccessor latest,
                  java.time.temporal.TemporalAccessor oldest,
                  int batchSize)
        Creates a new cursor. Latest and oldest point in time are formatted using the NSApi.DATETIME_PATTERN_ENTRY pattern.
        Parameters:
        api - Nightscout API instance
        path - API path used with NSApi.createGet(String). Has to return an array of json objects.
        dateField - the name of the field which holds information about the date and time of your data object
        latest - latest point in time to load data for
        oldest - oldest point in time to load data for
        batchSize - amount of entries which will be loaded at once

        public boolean hasNext()
        Checks if there is more data. May block the thread to request new data from the Nightscout server. Logs exceptions using NSApi.LOGGER.

      • next

        public JsonObject next()
        Gets the next object of the current buffer. Note that this method will never block, but may return null if not used in conjunction with this#hasNext() as the buffer will only be refreshed by that method.
        Specified by:
        next in interface java.util.Iterator<JsonElement>
        Returns:
